            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What is NCBI?</h3>
                <p>NCBI (National Center for Biotechnology Information) provides access to biomedical and genomic information. It is part of the National Institutes of Health (NIH) and offers various tools and resources for researchers and the public.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How can I search for scientific articles?</h3>
                <p>You can use PubMed, a free search engine provided by NCBI, to find scientific articles. Visit <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/">PubMed</a> and use keywords or phrases to search for articles.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How do I contact support?</h3>
                <p>If you need assistance, you can contact our support team via the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/contact/">NCBI Contact Page</a>.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

